        "text": "Model We are asked to find the magnetic field due to a simple current distribution, so this example is a typical problem for which the Biot—Savart law is appropriate. We must fi nd the field contribution from a small element of current and then integrate over the current distribution from θ1 to θ2, as shown in Figure 29.3b.",
